The House Committee on Health offers the following substitute to HB 54:
A BILL TO BE ENTITLED
AN ACT
1 To amend Titles 16, 31, 43, and 48 of the Official Code of Georgia Annotated, relating to
2 crimes and offenses, health, professions and businesses, and revenue and taxation,
3 respectively, so as to authorize licensed physician assistants to order home healthcare
4 services to patients of licensed home health agencies; to provide for definitions; to provide
5 for the approval of continuing education regarding death certificates; to provide for tax
6 credits for qualified caregiving expenses to include licensed physicians assistants; to provide
7 for related matters; to repeal conflicting laws; and for other purposes.
8 BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF GEORGIA:
9 SECTION 1.
10 Title 16 of the Official Code of Georgia Annotated, relating to crimes and offenses, is
11 amended by revising paragraph (4.2) of Code Section 16-13-72, relating to the sale,
12 distribution, or possession of dangerous drugs, as follows:
13 "(4.2) A registered professional nurse licensed under Article 1 of Chapter 26 of Title 43
14 who is employed or engaged by a licensed home health agency may possess sterile saline,
15 sterile water, and diluted heparin for use as intravenous maintenance for use in a home
16 health setting, and such nurse may administer such items to patients of the home health
