43 SECTION 3.
44 Such title is further amended by revising Code Section 31-7-150, relating to definitions, as
45 follows:
46 "31-7-150.
47 As used in this article, the term:
48 (1) 'Branch office' means a location or site, identified in the application or endorsement
49 thereto, from which a home health agency provides services within a portion of the total
50 geographic area served by the parent agency and which is part of the home health agency
51 and is located sufficiently close to share administration, supervision, and services in a
52 manner that renders it unnecessary for the branch independently to meet the requirements
53 of this article.
54 (1.1)(2) 'Department' means the Department of Community Health.
55 (2)(3) 'Home health agency' means a public, nonprofit, or proprietary organization,
56 whether owned or operated by one or more persons or legal entities, which is engaged in
57 furnishing home health healthcare services.
58 (3)(4) 'Home health healthcare services' means those items and services furnished to an
59 individual according to a written plan of treatment signed by the patient's physician, or
60 a licensed physician assistant acting pursuant to the authority of subsection (e.1) of Code
61 Section 43-34-103; by a home health agency,; or by others under arrangement with the
62 home health agency, on a visit or hourly basis, in a place of temporary or permanent
63 residence used as the individual's home, as follows:
64 (A) Part-time or intermittent skilled nursing care as ordered by a physician or a
65 licensed physician assistant acting pursuant to the authority of subsection (e.1) of Code
66 Section 43-34-103 and provided by or under the supervision of a registered nurse and
67 at least one other service listed in subparagraphs (B) through (D) of this paragraph;
68 (B) Physical, occupational, or speech therapy;
69 (C) Medical social services; and
