93 SECTION 4.
94 Said title is further amended by revising Code Section 31-7-153, relating to standards for
95 patient care and agency operation, regulations as to issuance, denial, suspension, or
96 revocation of licenses, and hearings, as follows:
97 "31-7-153.
98 The department shall promulgate regulations which define standards for the care, treatment,
99 health, safety, welfare, and comfort of patients served by home health agencies and for the
100 maintenance and operation of home health agencies which will promote safe and adequate
101 care and treatment of the patients. These regulations shall be no less stringent than those
102 required for participation of home health agencies in the Title XVIII medicare Medicare
103 program and shall include, but not be limited to, a provision requiring the agency to have
104 policies established by a professional group which includes at least one physician and one
105 registered nurse and appropriate representation from other professional disciplines;
106 provisions governing the services the agency provides; provisions for the supervision of
107 services by a physician, a licensed physician assistant, or a registered nurse, as appropriate,
108 and maintenance of clinical records on all patients, including a plan of treatment prescribed
109 by a physician. The department is authorized to issue, deny, suspend, or revoke licenses
110 in accordance with regulations promulgated pursuant to this Code section. Such
111 regulations shall also include hearing procedures related to denial, suspension, or
112 revocation of licenses."
