125 SECTION 6.
126 Title 43 of the Official Code of Georgia Annotated, relating to professions and businesses,
127 is amended by revising paragraph (1) of subsection (b) of Code Section 43-34-23, relating
128 to the delegation of authority to nurse or physician assistant, and by adding a new paragraph
129 to read as follows:
130 "(b)(1)(A) A physician may delegate the authority contained in subparagraph (B) of
131 this paragraph (b)(1)(B) of this Code section to:
132 (i) A licensed physician assistant in accordance with a job description; or
133 (ii) A nurse recognized by the Georgia Board of Nursing as a certified nurse midwife,
134 certified registered nurse anesthetist, certified nurse practitioner, or clinical nurse
135 specialist in psychiatric/mental health in accordance with a nurse protocol.
136 (B) A physician may delegate to those healthcare professionals identified in
137 subparagraph (A) of this paragraph (b)(1)(A) of this Code section:
138 (i) The authority to order controlled substances selected from a formulary of such
139 drugs established by the board and the authority to order dangerous drugs, medical
140 treatments, and diagnostic studies;
141 (ii) The authority to request, receive, and sign for professional samples and to
142 distribute professional samples to patients. The office or facility at which the
143 healthcare professional identified in subparagraph (A) of this paragraph (b)(1)(A) of
144 this Code section is working shall maintain a general list of the professional samples
