169 Title 48 of the Official Code of Georgia Annotated, relating to revenue and taxation, is
170 amended by revising paragraph (1) of subsection (a) of Code Section 48-7-29.2, relating to
171 tax credits for qualified caregiving expenses, as follows:
172 "(1) 'Qualified caregiving expenses' means payments by the taxpayer for home health
173 agency services, personal care services, personal care attendant services, homemaker
174 services, adult day care, respite care, or healthcare equipment and supplies which
175 equipment and supplies have been determined to be medically necessary by a physician
176 or a licensed physician assistant acting pursuant to the authority of subsection (e.1) of
177 Code Section 43-34-103, which services, care, or equipment and supplies are:
178 (A) Provided to the qualifying family member; and
179 (B) Purchased or obtained from an organization or individual not related to the
180 taxpayer or the qualifying family member."
